Cash overhead is a non-GAAP financial measure. We believe this information is
useful to investors in understanding the underlying operational performance of
the Company, its business and performance trends. Specifically, we believe that
the reduction in total cash overhead shows investors the cash savings achieved
by management through various restructuring initiatives. Although we believe
disclosure of total cash overhead enhances investors` understanding of our
business and performance, this non-GAAP financial measure should not be
considered an alternative to GAAP basis financial measures.

                                                                                                                                     
